text.tspan: The spatial raster captures the coverage and the resolution
of the data. An example would be a setup that spreads
across a whole continent with plot size study areas. It only
makes sense if the resolution is smaller than the coverage.
(point: m^2, plot: 1 m^2 - 0.01 km^2, region: 0.01 km^2 - 10.000 km^2,
